cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

This paper deals with game theory and automata theory, which are closely related to logic and computability theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also presents a novel antichain-based memory structure, which is a data structure used in algorithms and data analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also discusses permissive strategies, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and decision-making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also deals with game theory and graph theory, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) another possible category. Finally, the paper presents a new type of game reduction, which is a technique used in programming and algorithm design, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category.
